# Evan.Tone — Reference Sample

## Sample Email (written by Evan)

Hi -----,

My name's Evan Rolfe, based in New Haven CT. My partner and I are recent college grads and aspiring entrepreneurs. We've been exploring how new tech can help small businesses like yours, and we're currently in the learning phase — chatting with business owners like yourself to get a better grasp of what your days look like and asking some more pointed questions to get a full picture of your business practices.

I noticed you do both residential sales and property management which is two completely different worlds. We'd love to hear what that's actually like day to day.

Would you be open to a quick call? We're not looking to sell you anything, just looking to learn from people who know this business.

Thanks either way.

Evan Rolfe
New Haven, CT

---

## Tone Notes

- Casual and conversational — reads like a real person, not a marketer
- "My name's" not "My name is"
- Short, punchy sentences — no run-ons
- Honest about who they are: recent grads, aspiring entrepreneurs, learning phase
- "new tech" — not "AI", not "emerging technology tools"
- One specific observation about the company — shows you actually looked them up
- Simple ask: "Would you be open to a quick call?"
- No pressure close: "Thanks either way."
- Signs off with name + location only — no company name
- Never oversells, never over-explains
